## Data Flow

### Request Lifecycle
1. Client sends HTTPS request to `{{WEB_ENTRY}}`
2. {{WEB_ENTRY}} proxies API requests to `{{API_SERVER}}`
3. {{API_SERVER}} authenticates via {{AUTH_METHOD}}
4. {{API_SERVER}} reads/writes to {{DATABASE_TYPE}} via {{ORM_NAME}}
5. For long-running tasks, {{API_SERVER}} enqueues job to Redis
6. {{WORKER_NAME}} picks up job, processes, updates status

### Auth Flow
1. User POSTs credentials to `{{AUTH_ENDPOINT}}`
2. Server validates against {{AUTH_STORE}}
3. Server returns {{TOKEN_TYPE}} token
4. Client includes token in `{{AUTH_HEADER}}` header
5. {{AUTH_MIDDLEWARE}} validates on each request

